## Expressions, basic operations, elements (single)


I.e. R as a calculator

```{r,echo=T}
 6+3
 6**3 
 6^3
(2*(13.4+5))/48
```



## type of elements: numeric, character, logical, integer
```{r,echo=T}
is.numeric(4); is.character(4); is.logical(4)
as.numeric("0345") ;as.character(0345)
is.character(TRUE); is.logical(TRUE)
is.integer(as.integer(38)); is.character(pi)
is.numeric(pi); pi; format(pi, digits = 12)
is.numeric(format(pi, digits = 12))
as.numeric(format(pi, digits = 12))
```


## Operations: aritmethical, logical, paste


```{r,echo=T}

2+4; 2*4; 2**4; 2/4;  2==4 ; 2 != 4; !( 2 != 4);
2<= 4; 2<4; (1>2) & (1< 7) ; (1>2) | (1< 7);
```

## Objects, assignment

```{r,echo=T}
 answer <- 4 + 6
 answer
4+8-> answer
3*(6-7**2)/3 -> answer2
 answer + answer2

```

## list objects, remove objects


```{r,echo=T}
