## Character, strings

```{r, echo=T}

ca = "Barcelona"
substring(ca,2,5)
paste("Bar", "celona",sep="-") 
paste("Bar", as.character(1:5),sep="-") 
paste("Bar",1:5,sep="-")
```


## Format for numeric objects


```{r,echo=T}

format(exp(1), digits = 14)
## The golden ratio:
 phi= (1+sqrt(5))/2
 phi**2;   1/phi
 format(phi, digits = 20)
  format(1/phi, digits = 20)
  ## compare the two above
  ##  notice  machine discrepancy on decimal digits
 x = 4;   D <- 1/sqrt(x) ; D
 signif(pi, 4) ; trunc(pi) ; ceiling(pi) 

```
since R uses finite precision arithmetic, your answers aren’t accurate beyond 15 or 16 decimal places, so in general, more digits precision aren’t required.


## Vectors


```{r,echo=TRUE}
rep(4,10)
   a <- 2:14
  a = rep(TRUE,5)
  is.character(a)
   is.logical(a)
   a = rep("TR",5)
   is.character(a)
  seq(from=3,to=13,by=2)
 seq(3,13,2.3)
  seq(13,3, -2)
  seq(13,3)
seq(13,3, length =15)
 seq(6)
```


## Matrices

```{r,echo=T}

 a = 1:15
 mat1 = matrix(a, nrow=3, ncol=5);  mat1
 colnames(mat1) = c("col1","col2","col3","col4", "col5")
 rownames(mat1) = c("row1","row2","row3" )
 mat1
  paste("col",as.character(1:5),sep=" ")
  paste("col",as.character(1:5),sep="-")
  paste("col",as.character(1:5),sep="")
  mat1/3
```



## matrices operations 

```{r,echo=T}
mat2= round(mat1/3,2)
  mat1 + mat2;  mat1-mat2; mat1*mat2; mat1**mat2
  t(mat2)     # transpose of a matrix
  mat1 %*%t(mat2)     # matrix multiplication
```
There are other operations for matrices, monadic and diadic (to be discussed later in the course, as the inverse of a matrix, eigen values and eigen vectors, etc. )


## List

It is a *list* of objects


```{r,echo=T}
x <- list(values=sin(1:6), ids=letters[1:4], log=rep(TRUE,8)) 
x
```
```{r,echo=T}
x$extra <- "EXTRA"
length(x)
x[1]
x[["values"]]
str(x)
```


## Data frame 


Data frame is like a matrix but with possibility for different type of data in the different columns (set of vectors, the columns of the data frame, of the same length). Most of the time, importing data in R will be as a data frame.


```{r,echo=T}

 x <- list(values=sin(1:3), ids=letters[1:3],
log=rep(TRUE,3))
datax = data.frame(x)
datax

```

## List (advanced)

```{r,echo=T}

 d <- data.frame(a=11:13, b=21:23)
is.list(d)
str(d)
m <- lm(a ~  b, data=d) 
list(m)
str(m)
```


